SLIDE 1: TWIN CORE - Vision & Strategic Role
Twin Core is the Federated Backbone and the Orchestrator of the Digital Twin. It ensures the interoperability and cooperation of AIs across the Group.

The Orchestrator & Federator: Twin Core does not create local business value. It acts as an ecosystem with variable geometry that adapts to each franchise's maturity. It orchestrates distributed intelligence, enabling agents to collaborate without forcing the systematic centralization of raw data.

The Foundation Provider (Platform & AI): Twin Core designs, maintains, and provides state-of-the-art infrastructure (Knowledge Graph, Vector/Graph Knowledge Base, Agentic Platform) to accelerate the business's Time-to-Market.

The Advanced AI & R&D Engine: Twin Core leads the innovation effort in advanced artificial intelligence (GNN, Neurosymbolic AI, Hypergraphs). By hosting the topological truth and setting cognitive standards, it develops the advanced algorithms needed to understand the IT system's dynamics, paving the way for future concepts like the World Model.

SLIDE 2: TWIN CORE - Provided Assets (The Catalog)
Following a "Franchisor" logic, Twin Core provides ready-to-use accelerators, separating a mandatory core (for communication) and an "à la carte" data core.

The Mandatory Agentic Core (The Common Thread):

Central Agentic Platform (LangGraph): The orchestration infrastructure and the Central Catalog (Agentic Registry). This is the mandatory gateway for local AIs to be referenced, secured, and able to cooperate.

The Variable Geometry Data Core (À la carte):

Knowledge Graph (KG) Platform: The central graph database currently built on two major foundations: IT Topology and operational Events (alerts, incidents). It will gradually be enriched with new dimensions.

Knowledge Base (KB) Platform: An advanced cognitive solution based on a GraphRAG architecture (combining Vector search + Memgraph). It ingests unstructured documentation (Wikis, procedures) and makes it directly actionable for AIs.

An AI Engine Portfolio (R&D):

Off-the-shelf cognitive engines. The first active one is the "Correlation Engine" (dynamically linking Incidents and Changes), paving the way for other systemic analysis algorithms.

SLIDE 3: TWIN CORE - Consumption Model & Responsibilities
How does a franchise integrate with Twin Core? (The Acceleration Journey)
Twin Core provides the tools and infrastructure at every stage of the franchise lifecycle.

1. BUILD (Design & DevX):
The franchise doesn't start from scratch. It uses our Agentic Platform in a dedicated development environment (DevX) including the "Starter-Kit". To accelerate AI creation, it leverages our Coding Agents following the SDD (Specification Driven Development) methodology.

2. CONNECT & INGEST (Deployment & Data):

Agent Side: The franchise deploys its qualified agents into our secure execution environment (LangGraph) and references them in our Agentic Registry.

Data Side: The franchise provides its business data and documentation. Our ingestion factories dynamically integrate them into the Knowledge Graph (KG) and Knowledge Base (KB / GraphRAG).

3. QUERY & COOPERATE (Interrogation & Orchestration):
Local agents query our global platforms (Topology, Events, KB) to enrich their analysis context, without copying data. In return, our Central Orchestrator can solicit franchise agents to solve cross-domain use cases.

Rules of Engagement (DO'S & DON'TS)

DO: Twin Core provides the software factory (DevX, Ingestion Pipelines, Runtime) and orchestrates systemic routing.

DON'T (Variable Geometry): Twin Core does not force the centralization of raw business data (Raw Data).

DON'T (Business Value): Twin Core does not develop the logic for expert business agents (Business Oriented AI). This is the exclusive responsibility of the franchise.

DON'T (Local Governance): Twin Core is not responsible for the quality and curation of the business data or documentation injected by the franchise into the KB.
